# Coding Standards

## General
- KISS ‚Äî simplest solution that works
- DRY ‚Äî if you write it twice, extract it
- SOLID ‚Äî single responsibility, no god components
- No magic values ‚Äî all constants in `src/utils/constants.js`

```js
// ‚ùå BAD
<section className="py-24">

// ‚úÖ GOOD ‚Äî use a consistent spacing token via CSS var
<section className="py-[var(--spacing-section)]">
```

## No Magic Strings
```js
// ‚ùå BAD
<a href="mailto:hello@vantagewebdesigns.com">

// ‚úÖ GOOD
import { CONTACT_EMAIL } from '@/utils/constants'
<a href={`mailto:${CONTACT_EMAIL}`}>
```

## File Naming
- Components: `PascalCase.jsx`
- Utilities: `camelCase.js`
- Constants: `SCREAMING_SNAKE_CASE` inside the file

## PageSpeed ‚Äî Hard Rule (Target: 98-100 across all Core Vitals)
This codebase has been verified at 100/100/100/100 on PageSpeed Insights (desktop). Mobile targets 95+.
- `next/image` always ‚Äî never `<img>`. Always set `width`, `height`, `alt`
- Above-fold / hero images MUST have `priority` prop (eliminates LCP penalty)
- Hero image MUST use responsive `sizes` ‚Äî never `sizes="100vw"` alone:
  ```jsx
  sizes="(max-width: 640px) 640px, (max-width: 1024px) 1024px, 1920px"
  ```
- Background/decorative images use `quality={60}` ‚Äî heavily overlaid images don't need high quality
- Content images use `quality={75}`
- `next/font` always ‚Äî never `@import` in CSS (eliminates render-blocking font requests)
- Default to Server Components ‚Äî `'use client'` only when hooks/events/browser APIs are strictly needed
- No third-party scripts unless loaded via `next/script` with `strategy="lazyOnload"`
- No CSS `@import` inside component files ‚Äî all styles via Tailwind or `globals.css`
- Avoid layout shift: always provide explicit dimensions for images and media
- Use native `<details>/<summary>` for accordions ‚Äî zero JS, accessible, no bundle cost

## Accessibility ‚Äî Hard Rule (Target: 100)
- Heading order must be sequential ‚Äî never skip from h2 to h4
- `--color-muted` must maintain minimum 4.5:1 contrast ratio on dark backgrounds
- Current value `#c0c0cc` on `#09090f` passes WCAG AA ‚Äî do not darken it
- Never use `text-muted` on semi-transparent backgrounds (e.g. fixed header over hero image)
  Lighthouse calculates contrast against the actual rendered background including images beneath
  Use `text-text/70` instead ‚Äî it's relative to the text color and always passes on dark backgrounds
- Never use opacity modifiers on muted text (e.g. `text-muted/60`) ‚Äî the blended color often fails contrast
  Use full `text-muted` and rely on `line-through` or other visual cues for hierarchy instead

## Animations ‚Äî GPU Composited Only
- Never animate `background-position`, `background-size`, `width`, `height`, `top`, `left` ‚Äî these trigger paint/layout
- Only animate `transform` and `opacity` ‚Äî these are GPU composited and don't cause reflow
- The `logo-shine` animation uses `transform: translateX()` on a `::after` pseudo-element ‚Äî this is intentional
- Add `will-change: transform` sparingly and only when animation is known to run

## Comments
- No comments that describe what code does
- Only comment non-obvious intent or constraints

## No Em Dashes
- Never use em dashes (‚Äî) in copywriting ‚Äî they look AI-generated
- Use hyphens or rephrase the sentence instead
